{"id": "77b11399-a536-4e7b-8eb5-8a49f166a425", "task_id": "c54f3446-7976-4de3-88ca-56542f77eacf", "path": "templates/index.html", "artifact_type": "file", "content": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>CYBERPUNK LOGIN_V.2.0</title>\n    <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Orbitron:wght@400;700&family=Share+Tech+Mono&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <style>\n        :root {\n            --dark-bg: #0d0d1a;\n            --main-neon-blue: #00e5ff;\n            --main-neon-pink: #ff00ff;\n            --text-color: #e0e0e0;\n            --border-color: #00aaff;\n            --input-bg: rgba(2, 2, 20, 0.6);\n            --form-bg: rgba(10, 10, 30, 0.8);\n            --glow-spread: 0 0 15px var(--main-neon-blue), 0 0 30px var(--main-neon-pink);\n        }\n\n        *, *::before, *::after {\n            box-sizing: border-box;\n            margin: 0;\n            padding: 0;\n        }\n\n        body {\n            font-family: 'Share Tech Mono', monospace;\n            background-color: var(--dark-bg);\n            color: var(--text-color);\n            display: flex;\n            justify-content: center;\n            align-items: center;\n            min-height: 100vh;\n            overflow: hidden;\n            position: relative;\n            background-image: radial-gradient(circle at center, rgba(0, 229, 255, 0.05) 0%, transparent 70%);\n            background-size: 100% 100%;\n        }\n\n        body::before {\n            content: '';\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n            background: repeating-linear-gradient(\n                0deg,\n                transparent,\n                transparent 1px,\n                rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.05) 1px,\n                rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.05) 2px\n            ),\n            repeating-linear-gradient(\n                90deg,\n                transparent,\n                transparent 1px,\n                rgba(255, 0, 255, 0.05) 1px,\n                rgba(255, 0, 255, 0.05) 2px\n            );\n            pointer-events: none;\n            opacity: 0.3;\n            animation: scanline 8s infinite linear;\n        }\n\n        @keyframes scanline {\n            0% {\n                background-position: 0% 0%;\n            }\n            100% {\n                background-position: 0% 100%;\n            }\n        }\n\n        .login-container {\n            position: relative;\n            z-index: 10;\n            padding: 20px;\n            max-width: 400px;\n            width: 90%;\n            background: var(--form-bg);\n            border: 2px solid var(--border-color);\n            box-shadow: var(--glow-spread);\n            border-radius: 8px;\n            text-align: center;\n            animation: appear 1s ease-out forwards;\n        }\n\n        @keyframes appear {\n            from {\n                opacity: 0;\n                transform: translateY(-50px) scale(0.9);\n            }\n            to {\n                opacity: 1;\n                transform: translateY(0) scale(1);\n            }\n        }\n\n        h1 {\n            font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;\n            font-size: 3em;\n            color: var(--main-neon-blue);\n            text-transform: uppercase;\n            margin-bottom: 30px;\n            position: relative;\n            text-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--main-neon-blue), 0 0 20px var(--main-neon-pink);\n        }\n\n        h1.glitch {\n            animation: glitch-skew 3s infinite linear alternate-reverse;\n        }\n\n        h1.glitch::before,\n        h1.glitch::after {\n            content: attr(data-text);\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n        }\n\n        h1.glitch::before {\n            color: var(--main-neon-pink);\n            left: -2px;\n            text-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--main-neon-pink);\n            animation: glitch-anim-1 2s infinite linear alternate-reverse;\n        }\n\n        h1.glitch::after {\n            color: var(--main-neon-blue);\n            left: 2px;\n            text-shadow: 0 0 10px var(--main-neon-blue);\n            animation: glitch-anim-2 3s infinite linear alternate-reverse;\n        }\n\n        @keyframes glitch-anim-1 {\n            0% {\n                clip-path: inset(30% 0 70% 0);\n            }\n            20% {\n                clip-path: inset(80% 0 10% 0);\n            }\n            40% {\n                clip-path: inset(10% 0 80% 0);\n            }\n            60% {\n                clip-path: inset(40% 0 30% 0);\n            }\n            80% {\n                clip-path: inset(70% 0 20% 0);\n            }\n            100% {\n                clip-path: inset(5% 0 85% 0);\n            }\n        }\n\n        @keyframes glitch-anim-2 {\n            0% {\n                clip-path: inset(20% 0 75% 0);\n            }\n            25% {\n                clip-path: inset(60% 0 30% 0);\n            }\n            50% {\n                clip-path: inset(5% 0 85% 0);\n            }\n            75% {\n                clip-path: inset(90% 0 0% 0);\n            }\n            100% {\n                clip-path: inset(30% 0 60% 0);\n            }\n        }\n\n        @keyframes glitch-skew {\n            0% {\n                transform: skew(0deg);\n            }\n            2% {\n                transform: skew(-2deg);\n            }\n            4% {\n                transform: skew(2deg);\n            }\n            6% {\n                transform: skew(0deg);\n            }\n            20% {\n                transform: skew(-0.5deg);\n            }\n            22% {\n                transform: skew(0.5deg);\n            }\n            24% {\n                transform: skew(0deg);\n            }\n            40% {\n                transform: skew(1deg);\n            }\n            42% {\n                transform: skew(-1deg);\n            }\n            44% {\n                transform: skew(0deg);\n            }\n            60% {\n                transform: skew(-1.5deg);\n            }\n            62% {\n                transform: skew(1.5deg);\n            }\n            64% {\n                transform: skew(0deg);\n            }\n            80% {\n                transform: skew(0.75deg);\n            }\n            82% {\n                transform: skew(-0.75deg);\n            }\n            84% {\n                transform: skew(0deg);\n            }\n        }\n\n\n        .input-group {\n            margin-bottom: 20px;\n            text-align: left;\n        }\n\n        label {\n            display: block;\n            margin-bottom: 8px;\n            color: var(--main-neon-blue);\n            font-size: 0.9em;\n            text-transform: uppercase;\n            text-shadow: 0 0 5px rgba(0, 229, 255, 0.5);\n        }\n\n        input[type=\"text\"],\n        input[type=\"password\"] {\n            width: 100%;\n            padding: 12px 15px;\n            background-color: var(--input-bg);\n            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);\n            border-radius: 4px;\n            color: var(--text-color);\n            font-family: 'Share Tech Mono', monospace;\n            font-size: 1em;\n            transition: all 0.3s ease;\n            box-shadow: inset 0 0 5px rgba(0, 229, 255, 0.3);\n        }\n\n        input[type=\"text\"]:focus,\n        input[type=\"password\"]:focus {\n            border-color: var(--main-neon-pink);\n            box-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--main-neon-pink), inset 0 0 8px var(--main-neon-pink);\n            outline: none;\n            background-color: rgba(2, 2, 20, 0.8);\n        }\n\n        button {\n            width: 100%;\n            padding: 15px;\n            background: linear-gradient(45deg, var(--main-neon-blue), var(--main-neon-pink));\n            border: none;\n            border-radius: 4px;\n            color: #fff;\n            font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;\n            font-size: 1.2em;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            text-transform: uppercase;\n            cursor: pointer;\n            transition: all 0.3s ease;\n            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 229, 255, 0.7);\n            position: relative;\n            overflow: hidden;\n        }\n\n        button::before {\n            content: '';\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: -100%;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);\n            transform: skewX(-30deg);\n            transition: left 0.5s ease;\n        }\n\n        button:hover::before {\n            left: 100%;\n        }\n\n        button:hover {\n            box-shadow: 0 0 20px var(--main-neon-blue), 0 0 40px var(--main-neon-pink);\n            transform: translateY(-2px) scale(1.02);\n            filter: brightness(1.2);\n        }\n\n        button:active {\n            transform: translateY(0) scale(1);\n            filter: brightness(1);\n            box-shadow: 0 0 5px var(--main-neon-blue), 0 0 10px var(--main-neon-pink);\n        }\n\n        .footer-text {\n            margin-top: 30px;\n            font-size: 0.8em;\n            color: rgba(224, 224, 224, 0.6);\n            text-shadow: 0 0 3px var(--main-neon-blue);\n            animation: fadein 2s ease-in forwards 1s;\n            opacity: 0;\n        }\n\n        @keyframes fadein {\n            from { opacity: 0; }\n            to { opacity: 1; }\n        }\n\n        .current-time {\n            font-size: 0.8em;\n            color: var(--main-neon-blue);\n            margin-top: 15px;\n            text-shadow: 0 0 5px var(--main-neon-blue);\n        }\n\n        @media (max-width: 600px) {\n            h1 {\n                font-size: 2.5em;\n            }\n            .login-container {\n                padding: 15px;\n                width: 95%;\n            }\n            button {\n                font-size: 1.1em;\n                padding: 12px;\n            }\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"login-container\">\n        <h1 class=\"glitch\" data-text=\"LOGIN\">LOGIN</h1>\n        <form id=\"loginForm\" action=\"/login\" method=\"POST\">\n            <div class=\"input-group\">\n                <label for=\"username\">[[ USERNAME ]]</label>\n                <input type=\"text\" id=\"username\" name=\"username\" required autocomplete=\"off\">\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"input-group\">\n                <label for=\"password\">[[ PASSWORD ]]</label>\n                <input type=\"password\" id=\"password\" name=\"password\" required autocomplete=\"off\">\n            </div>\n            <button type=\"submit\">ACCESS</button>\n        </form>\n        <p class=\"current-time\" id=\"currentTime\">SYSTEM TIME: LOADING...</p>\n        <p class=\"footer-text\">_SYS_VER. 2.0.4.5_ // _SEC_PROTOCOL_ACTIVE_</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {\n            const loginForm = document.getElementById('loginForm');\n            const currentTimeElement = document.getElementById('currentTime');\n\n            // Update current time\n            function updateTime() {\n                const now = new Date();\n                const options = {\n                    year: 'numeric',\n                    month: '2-digit',\n                    day: '2-digit',\n                    hour: '2-digit',\n                    minute: '2-digit',\n                    second: '2-digit',\n                    hour12: false\n                };\n                const formattedTime = now.toLocaleString('en-GB', options).replace(/,/g, ''); // Format: DD/MM/YYYY HH:MM:SS\n                currentTimeElement.textContent = `SYSTEM TIME: ${formattedTime}`;\n            }\n\n            // Initial call and set interval for time update\n            updateTime();\n            setInterval(updateTime, 1000);\n\n            // Basic form submission handler\n            loginForm.addEventListener('submit', (event) => {\n                event.preventDefault(); // Prevent default form submission\n\n                const username = document.getElementById('username').value;\n                const password = document.getElementById('password').value;\n\n                console.log('Attempting login...');\n                console.log('Username:', username);\n                console.log('Password:', '*'.repeat(password.length)); // Mask password for console output\n\n                // In a real application, you would send this data to the backend via fetch API\n                // Example:\n                /*\n                fetch('/login', {\n                    method: 'POST',\n                    headers: {\n                        'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n                    },\n                    body: JSON.stringify({ username, password }),\n                })\n                .then(response => response.json())\n                .then(data => {\n                    if (data.success) {\n                        alert('Login successful!');\n                        // Redirect or update UI\n                    } else {\n                        alert('Login failed: ' + data.message);\n                    }\n                })\n                .catch((error) => {\n                    console.error('Error:', error);\n                    alert('An error occurred during login.');\n                });\n                */\n                alert('Login functionality is currently simulated. Check console for input values.');\n            });\n        });\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>", "patches": [], "metadata": {"language": "html", "framework": "static_html", "explanation": "This HTML file (`templates/index.html`) implements a cyberpunk-themed login page using standard HTML5, CSS3, and Vanilla JavaScript. The design features a dark background with neon blue and pink accents, monospaced fonts, and subtle animations to evoke a futuristic, slightly glitchy aesthetic.\n\n**HTML Structure:**\n-   Includes a standard HTML5 boilerplate with `meta` tags for character set and viewport.\n-   Imports Google Fonts ('Orbitron' for titles and 'Share Tech Mono' for general text) to achieve a distinct cyberpunk look.\n-   The main content is wrapped in a `div.login-container` which is centrally aligned.\n-   A `h1` element with a `glitch` class and `data-text` attribute creates a dynamically animated title.\n-   A `form` with `username` and `password` input fields, each within an `input-group` for consistent styling.\n-   A `button` for submission, also designed with a neon glow and hover effect.\n-   A `p` element displays a dynamically updated `SYSTEM TIME` and another for a `_SYS_VER_` footer message.\n\n**CSS Styling:**\n-   Uses CSS variables for easy theme customization (colors, backgrounds, etc.).\n-   The `body` is styled with a dark background, centered content, and includes subtle repeating linear gradients (`::before`) for a scanline/grid effect.\n-   The `.login-container` and `.login-box` (implicitly, as login-container acts as the box) feature a translucent dark background, neon borders, and glowing `box-shadow`.\n-   The `h1.glitch` utilizes `::before` and `::after` pseudo-elements with `clip-path` and keyframe animations (`glitch-anim-1`, `glitch-anim-2`, `glitch-skew`) to create a vibrant, flickering text effect.\n-   Input fields have a dark, translucent background, neon borders, and glowing `box-shadow` on focus.\n-   The `button` has a gradient background, neon text, and a dynamic 'shine' effect on hover, along with a glow.\n-   Responsive adjustments are included for smaller screens.\n\n**Vanilla JavaScript:**\n-   Ensures the script runs after the DOM is fully loaded.\n-   Implements an `updateTime` function to display the current system time in a specified format, updating every second.\n-   Attaches an event listener to the login form to prevent its default submission. Instead, it logs the username and a masked password to the console and shows a simulated alert. A commented-out `fetch` API example is provided to illustrate how actual backend integration would typically work.", "dependencies": []}, "created_at": "2026-05-17 14:22:35.805913"}